        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>To explore the dust structure of the disk and search for gas, we will 
observe HD 38397 at 1.3mm continuum and at the J=2-1 line of different 
CO isotopologues. In BAND6 the continuum and the selected CO lines can 
be measured in one Science Goal. Our sensitivity requirement is based on 
modelling the expected 1.3mm continuum image of the source. According to 
our models the minimum total continuum flux of HD 38397 at this wavelength 
is ~1 mJy. Based on our simulations using the C36-2 configuration with a 
spatial resolution of ~0.8 arcsec, we expect a minimum flux of 85 microJy per 
beam. In order to detect the dust continuum emission from our source with a 
signal-to-noise ratio better than 6 we request a continuum sensitivity of 
14 microJy/beam. We note that to achieve the best signal-to-noise, we will 
combine the TDM observations with FDM data (using the line-free channels only) 
to compile the final continuum image (see also in Correlator Setup). To 
achieve the requested sensitivity we need 1.56 hours integration time 
(calculating with an aggregated bandwidth of 6.56 GHz). With this integration 
time and observational configuration for the CO lines we can detect 
2x10^{-6} M_Earth CO gas (see Preparatory work in the Science Justification).</prj:justificationText>
